So, basically you&#x27;re saying it&#x27;s OK that the abstraction layer for RethinkDB creates nasty code because it&#x27;s native JS? I don&#x27;t agree. I think nasty code is never OK.<p>Why can&#x27;t the RethinkDB abstraction layer just be better? Why isn&#x27;t:<p><pre><code>    var dateFilter = new Date();
    dateFilter = dateFilter.setDate(dateFilter.getDate() - 30);
    rdb.table(&#x27;users&#x27;).get([ { column: signup_date, gt: dateFilter } ]).each(function (err, user) {
        // Do stuff
    });
</code></pre>
Possible? That&#x27;s just off the top of my head how I would do it in a way that&#x27;s native JS and far better than what&#x27;s presented in the article.
